Summer Prep
Many home and business owners are looking for ways to make their HVAC systems more energy-efficient. Many HVAC customers provide energy-efficient alternatives. Check to see if your customer offers discounts on swapping to a more energy-efficient or newer model. Learn more »

Spring Maintenance
For many, A/C systems will click on for the first time since last summer. Scheduling routine maintenance can prevent pricey fixes down the road. Tasks often include: testing and cleaning the blower fan, checking the level of coolant in the cooling system, and testing the system’s thermostat and operation. Try creating content about tips on signs of A/C trouble or promoting routine maintenance checks. Learn more »

Summer heat
With summer ramping up, so do outside temperatures. Between May and June we see a sizeable increase in average temperature in areas that have typical summers. This means the need for potential emergency repairs, filter changes, and finding ways to keep homes cool without breaking the bank.
